Parse a wastd_api_response of taxon-conservationlisting to tbl_df

Source: R/parse_taxon-conservationlisting.R
parse_taxon_conservationlisting.Rd

Parse a wastd_api_response of taxon-conservationlisting to tbl_df

parse_taxon_conservationlisting(
  wastd_api_response,
  wastd_url = wastdr::get_wastd_url()
)

Arguments

wastd_api_response

A wastd_api_response of taxon-conservationlisting, e.g. get_wastd("taxon-conservationlisting").
wastd_url

The base URL for WAStD, default: get_wastd_url()

Value

A tbl_df with columns:

  • id <int> The TSC ID of the Conservation Listing

  • taxon <int> The WACensus NameID of the taxon

  • source <int> The TSC ID for the Source of the Conservation Listing.

  • source_id <chr> The original ID of the source as chr. Most sources will be an integer, uuid, or any other unique ID.

  • scope <int> The TSC ID for the legal scope of this Conservation Listing: State of Western Australia (0), Commonwealth of Austalia (1), International (2), or Action Plan (3).

  • status <int> The TSC ID of the approval status, e.g. listed (80), de-listed (90), rejected (100), or in stages of approval (0..70).

  • proposed_on <dttm> The date on which this Conservation Listing was proposed on (GMT+08).

  • effective_from <dttm> The date on which this Conservation Listing was effective from (GMT+08).

  • effective_to <dttm> The date on which this Conservation Listing was effective_to (GMT+08).

  • last_reviewed_on <dttm> The date on which this Conservation Listing was last reviewed on (GMT+08).

  • review_due <dttm> The date on which this Conservation Listing will be due for reviewed (GMT+08).

  • comments <chr> Any comments. Worth a read!

  • category_cache <chr> A human-readable representation of the conservation category (or categories).

  • criteria_cache <chr> A human-readable representation of the conservation criteria.

  • label <chr> An auto-generated label for the Conservation Listing.

  • category <lst> A list if TSC conservation category IDs.

  • criteria <lst> A list if TSC conservation criterion IDs.
